\title{Product of family of groups}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-13}
\taxon{definition}
\MML{group_7}{def 2}{K2}

\p{Let #{\{\mathcal{F}_{i}\}_{i\in I}} be a family of groups. We define the \define{Product Group} #{\prod_{i\in I}\mathcal{F}_{i}} whose underlying set is the product of the underlying sets of the family, where the binary operator is defined by, for any #{g,h\in \prod_{i\in I}\mathcal{F}_{i}},
##{(gh)_{i}=g_{i}h_{i}}
When #{I=\{1,2\}}, this recovers [[gr-000Z]].}